%!options(html): --outfile ../doc/xix_ref_checks.html

~B[Reference xix_ref.html]→[General xix_ref_gen.html]~E

Before creating the final output, it might be worth performing a few
pre-publication checks. We recommend the following:

+ See if there are any incorrectly overlapping pages using the
  [Combine Overlapping Pages Dialog xix_ref_dlg_combpages.html], or
  using the
  [Index→Check→Overlapping Pages action xix_ref_act_x_check.html#overlap],
  and editing manually and/or using the
  [Modify→Combine Pages action xix_ref_act_m_comb.html].
+ See if there are any entries that have a page number that's too high,
  or too large a page range, or too many pages, using the
  [Index→Check→Too High Page Number action xix_ref_act_x_check.html#high],
  the
  [Index→Check→Too Large Page Range action xix_ref_act_x_check.html#large],
  and the
  [Index→Check→Too Many Pages action xix_ref_act_x_check.html#many].
  (Note that all the ~KIndex→Check~E actions can be invoked in one go
  using the
  [Index→Check→All the Checks action xix_ref_act_x_check.html#all].)
+ See if there are any entries that don't have pages, subentries, or
  cross-references, using the
  [Main Window Filtered Panel xix_ref_panel_filter.html]'s
  [Without Pages or Subentries or Cross-References xix_ref_p_filt_pre.html#bare]
  filter.
+ See if there are any entries with both pages and one or more //see//
  cross-references, using the
  [Main Window Filtered Panel xix_ref_panel_filter.html]'s
  [Pages and See cross-reference(s) xix_ref_p_filt_pre.html#pagesee]
  filter.
+ See if there are any entries with just one subentry (e.g., maybe the
  subentry could be merged using the
  [Modify→Merge into Parent action xix_ref_act_m_mrg_p.html]), using the
  [Main Window Filtered Panel xix_ref_panel_filter.html]'s
  [Has One Subentry xix_ref_p_filt_pre.html#sub1] filter.
+ See if there are any entries (at the same level, i.e., both main
  entries, or both subentries of the same parent entry), whose terms are
  the same (even if their [Sort As Text xix_ref_sortas.html]s are
  different), regardless of their case and text styling, using the
  [Index→Check→Same Term Texts action xix_ref_act_x_check.html#same].
+ Review any double- or triple-posted (or more) entries, in case you want
  to turn any into cross-references. Use the
  [Main Window Filtered Panel xix_ref_panel_filter.html]'s
  [Linked Group xix_ref_p_filt_cust.html#linked] filter to see each
  linked groups entries in turn. If you unlink a linked group you'll be
  given the choice of leaving the pages intact for all entries in the
  group, or leaving one entry's pages and replacing the pages in the
  other entries with //see// cross-references to the one with pages.
  See the
  [Delete or Unlink Linked Group Dialog xix_ref_dlg_unlink.html].


