A useful pattern for adding missing cross-references shown in the
[Main Window Filtered Panel xix_ref_panel_filter.html] (e.g., with the
[Without Pages or Subentries or Cross-References xix_ref_p_filt_pre.html#bare]
filter), is to navigate to the target entry you want the cross-reference
to refer to, then use the [Goto→Filtered action xix_ref_act_g_filt.html]
to return to the original entry, and then use the
[Entry→Add Cross-reference action xix_ref_act_y_xref.html] to pop up the
[Add Cross-reference Dialog xix_ref_dlg_addxref.html]. The target entry
should be shown as the ~KRecent~E entry. (If this isn't the case you can
always circle the target using the
[Entry→Circle action xix_ref_act_y_circ.html].)
''</td></tr></table>''

If the output doesn't match your expectations in some way, review the
settings in all the [Output Options Dialog xix_ref_dlg_output.html]'s
tabs.

